'''Kiburi Shrine''' (きぶりじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Ōno|Q1203308|qid=Q1203308|1=Ōno, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Ibi District|Q1204309|qid=Q1204309|1=Ibi District, Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|qid=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}.

It is a {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} ({{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|qid=Q864156|lt=Mino no Kuni|1=Mino Province}} {{ill|lt=Ōno District (Mino)|Q11439757|qid=Q11439757|lt=Ōno District|1=Ōno district}} Kiburi Shrine, Shōnii ranked Shikinaisha Kiburi Ōkami), and its former rank under the {{ill|lt=Modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|qid=Q712534|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

===Enshrined deities===
*{{ill|lt=Izanagi|Q813858|qid=Q813858|lt=Izanagi-no-Mikoto|1=Izanagi}}
*{{ill|lt=Izanami|Q682306|qid=Q682306|lt=Izanami-no-Mikoto|1=Izanami}}
*{{ill|lt=Kikurihime-no-Kami|Q11619891|qid=Q11619891|lt=Kikuri-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Kikurihime}}
*{{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|qid=Q276944|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}}
*Hakusan Hosaō

===History===
According to shrine tradition, it was founded in {{ill|lt=725|Q23552|qid=Q23552|1=725}} ({{ill|lt=Jinki|Q1373210|qid=Q1373210|1=Jinki (era)}} 2). On lunar June 18 of Jinki 2, golden-colored snow reportedly fell on the summit of Mt. Hakusan in Ōno District of Mino Province. This phenomenon was interpreted by oracle as the descent of {{ill|lt=Kikurihime-no-Kami|Q11619891|qid=Q11619891|lt=Hakusan-hime-no-Kami|1=Kikurihime}}, and a shrine was built and worshiped on Mt. Hakusan summit. At this time, the nearby {{ill|lt=Hossō|Q349849|qid=Q349849|1=East Asian Yogācāra}} temple Shinpuku-ji was renamed {{ill|lt=Kiburi-ji|Q11523695|qid=Q11523695|1=Kiburi-ji}}.

In {{ill|lt=1530|Q6429|qid=Q6429|1=1530}} ({{ill|lt=Kyōroku|Q1193418|qid=Q1193418|1=Kyōroku}} 3), floods damaged buildings at the foot, and in {{ill|lt=1560|Q6613|qid=Q6613|1=1560}} ({{ill|lt=Eiroku|Q1143341|qid=Q1143341|1=Eiroku}} 3), it was burned by {{ill|lt=Oda Nobunaga|Q171411|qid=Q171411|1=Oda Nobunaga}}, and the temple complex was lost.

It was later restored with aid such as {{ill|lt=vermilion-seal letters|Q11093673|qid=Q11093673|1=shuinjō}} issued by {{ill|lt=Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Q187550|qid=Q187550|1=Toyotomi Hideyoshi}} and {{ill|lt=Tokugawa Ieyasu|Q171977|qid=Q171977|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu}}, and in {{ill|lt=1677|Q7631|qid=Q7631|1=1677}} ({{ill|lt=Enpō|Q1145735|qid=Q1145735|1=Enpō}} 5) new shrine buildings were constructed with support of the Toda clan of {{ill|lt=Ōgaki Domain|Q839430|qid=Q839430|1=Ōgaki Domain}}. Thereafter the Toda clan of Ōgaki Domain protected the shrine through repairs.

It had long stood on the summit of Hakusan (317 m), but because Hakusan area had high-quality {{ill|lt=limestone|Q23757|qid=Q23757|1=Limestone}}, {{ill|lt=lime|Q250423|qid=Q250423|1=Lime (material)}} mining began around the area from the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|qid=Q3125096}}. In {{ill|lt=1968|Q2644|qid=Q2644|1=1968}} (Shōwa 43), Hakusan was to be cut for mining, and Kiburi Shrine moved to its current site at the foot of the mountain.

In {{ill|lt=1999|Q2091|qid=Q2091|1=1999}} (Heisei 11), surrounding areas were developed as "Kiburi Fureai Park."

=== Cultural properties ===
*Town-designated cultural properties
**Chōzu stone (Important Cultural Property, craft)<ref name="onocho bunkazai">{{Cite web|和書|date= |url=http://heritage-ono.jp/shiteibunkazai.html |title=List of designated cultural properties |publisher=Ōno Town |accessdate=2013-04-20 |archivedate=2013-05-01 |archiveurl=https://archive.fo/tbePM}}</ref>
**Kiburi-bayashi (intangible folk cultural property)<ref name="onocho bunkazai"/>
**Fusulina fossils (natural monument)<ref name="onocho bunkazai"/>

=== Location ===
*Inatomi Aza Hakusan 2586, Ōno-chō, Ibi District, Gifu Prefecture

=== Transportation ===
*About 3.5 km from {{ill|lt=Motosu Station|Q6918526|qid=Q6918526|1=Motosu Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Tarumi Railway|Q11543718|qid=Q11543718|1=Tarumi Railway}}.
*About 3.5 km from {{ill|lt=Kochibora Station|Q6424878|qid=Q6424878|1=Kochibora Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Tarumi Railway|Q11543718|qid=Q11543718|1=Tarumi Railway}}.
*About 5 km from {{ill|lt=Ōno Bus Center|Q11439494|qid=Q11439494|1=Ōno Bus Center}} via {{ill|lt=Meihan Kintetsu Bus|Q11415818|qid=Q11415818|1=Meihan Kintetsu Bus}} / {{ill|lt=Gifu Bus|Q5560101|qid=Q5560101|lt=Gifu Bus|1=Gifu Bus}}.

